  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Spread your Biscoff on the first slice of bread, your peanut butter on the second, and Biscoff once again on the third. Stack them on top of each other."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Cut the crusts off so it forms a neat square."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Now create your egg mix. Combine your eggs, milk and a sprinkle of cinnamon, and mix well. Then, take your bread stack and dredge it in the egg mix on all sides."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Heat up your oil to 180-190°C. You can use a chopstick to test the temperature – if the oil starts bubbling right away when you put the chopsticks in, it’s ready."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Place the block of bread in the pan and fry each side for 1-2 mins until it turns golden brown."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Once it's looking all golden, remove the toast onto a drying rack or on a paper towel so that either the excess oil drips out or the towel soaks it up."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Serve with a knob of butter and a healthy drizzle of condensed milk."
    }
  ],
